==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ginger
<hw>Gin"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>ginger</ets>, <ets>gingever</ets>, <ets>gingivere</ets>, OF.
<ets>gengibre</ets>, <ets>gingimbre</ets>, F. <ets>gingembre</ets>, L.
<ets>zingiber</ets>, <ets>zingiberi</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/; of Oriental
origin; cf. Ar. & Pers. <ets>zenjeb⟦imac⟧l</ets>, fr. Skr.
<ets>⟦cced⟧⟦rsdot⟧⟦ndot⟧gav⟦eum⟧ra</ets>, prop., hornshaped;
<ets><?/<?/<?/ga</ets> horn + <ets>v⟦eum⟧ra</ets> body.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant of the genus
<gen>Zingiber</gen>, of the East and West Indies. The species most known
is <spn>Zingiber officinale</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The hot and spicy rootstock of <spn>Zingiber
officinale</spn>, which is much used in cookery and in
medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ginger ale</b></col> <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>a soft drink
flavored with ginger and carbonated.</cd> <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>See
<cref>ginger beer</cref>, below.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Ginger
beer</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>Ginger ale</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a
mild beer impregnated with ginger.</cd> -- <col><b>Ginger
cordial</b></col>, <cd>a liquor made from ginger, raisins, lemon rind,
and water, and sometimes whisky or brandy.</cd> -- <col><b>Ginger
pop</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Ginger ale</cref> (above).</cd> --
<col><b>Ginger wine</b></col>, <cd>wine impregnated with ginger.</cd> --
<col><b>Wild ginger</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>an American herb
(<spn>Asarum Canadense</spn>) with two reniform leaves and a long,
cordlike rootstock which has a strong taste of ginger.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gingerbread</ent>⟦br⟧
